c: 5
v: 18
t: "The Jews and the Christians say, \"We are God's children and His loved ones.\" Say to them, \"Why does He punish you for your sins? No, you are only human beings of His creation. He forgives whomever He wills, and He punishes whomever He wills, for God has control over the heavens and the earth and everything in between. All journeys lead to Him"